    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "A layer of vapor swirls just below the surface of this glass container holding a large, dried heap of fungal-encrusted seaweed. You can throw the phial up to 30 feet when you Activate it. When opened or thrown, a Medium sargassum heap effigy reconstitutes to release a hallucinogenic cloud in a 15-foot emanation, forcing each creature to attempt a DC 20 Fortitude save. On a failure, a creature rolls 1d4 to determine what it is hallucinating for the next 1d4 rounds (unless otherwise noted). At the beginning of their turn, an affected creature attempts a new save.\n1. The target thinks they are sinking through the floor. It falls prone and spends 1 action on its next turn flailing its limbs as if attempting to swim.\n2. The target thinks an item they are holding turns into a viper. The target Releases the item and spends its next turn fleeing from it.\n3. The target thinks they have shrunk to 1/10 their normal size. For 1 round, it is slowed 2, enfeebled 2, and takes a \u201310-foot status penalty to its Speed.\n4. The target believes they are melting. It drops everything it\u2019s holding and becomes slowed 2 and clumsy 2 for 1 round.",
        "level": 6,
        "image": {
            "type": "image",
            "name": "Sargassum Phial",
            "image": "Sargassum_Phial.webp"
        },
        "traits": [
